title: Girl Calls 911 After Her Mom Overdoses in Car
description: A 12-year-old girl in Volusia County, Florida called 911 after her mother lost consciousness behind the wheel, allegedly from a drug overdose. Inside the vehicle were also a seven-year-old and one-year-old. Authorities found them and saved the woman with Naloxone. The 28-year-old mother told police she took heroin for a long family drive because she had no pain killers and her back was hurting. The woman was taken to the hospital and will face charges.
